<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1436,1397,1590]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[208,336,1438,1464]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body fusiform; prodorsal shield without frontal lobe, scapular tubercles and setae absent; anterolateral setae on coxisternum I (
<emphasis box="[586,615,1481,1506]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">1b</emphasis>
) absent; leg tibia fused with tarsus; opisthosoma setae 
<emphasis box="[1260,1273,1481,1506]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">e</emphasis>
absent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1436,1397,1590]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
This genus consists of 2 species (
<bibRefCitation author="Amrine, J. W. Jr. &amp; Stasny, T. A. &amp; Flechtmann, C. H. W." box="[637,885,1522,1548]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" refId="ref44790" refString="Amrine, J. W. Jr., Stasny, T. A. &amp; Flechtmann, C. H. W. (2003) Revised keys to world genera of Eriophyoidea (Acari: Prostigmata). Indira Publishing House, Michigan, U. S. A., 244 pp." type="book" year="2003">
Amrine 
<emphasis box="[743,801,1522,1547]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">et al</emphasis>
. 2003
</bibRefCitation>
). Only one species has been recorded from Southeast Asia.
</paragraph>
